// Semantic direction:
// net_stdlib is the Norscode standard network library providing high-level TCP, HTTP, DNS, and gRPC APIs.
// tcp_listener binds and accepts incoming TCP connections; listener_accept blocks until a client connects.
// tcp_dialer creates outgoing TCP connections with configurable dial_timeout.
// http_server_std wraps a router and middleware_chain; http_server_shutdown gracefully closes active connections.
// http_client_std provides convenient client_get, client_post, and client_do methods with connection pooling.
// response_read_body consumes the full response body and closes the underlying connection.
// url_parse splits a URL string into scheme, host, port, path, query, and fragment.
// query_params is the parsed key-value map from the URL query string.
// query_encode serializes a query_params map back into a properly URL-encoded string.
// ip_is_private returns true for RFC 1918 addresses (10.x, 172.16-31.x, 192.168.x).
// cidr_contains checks whether an IP address falls within a CIDR block.
// cidr_network returns the network address (host bits zeroed); cidr_broadcast returns the broadcast address.
// error_connection_refused means no service is listening at the target address.
// error_connection_reset means the peer closed the connection with a TCP RST.
// nc net fetch makes an HTTP request from the command line and prints the response.
// cmd_net_serve starts a simple file-serving or echo HTTP server for development and testing.
// cmd_net_proxy starts a forward or reverse proxy with configurable rules.
// cmd_net_dns resolves a hostname and prints the resulting records.
// cmd_net_scan performs a port scan on a range of ports for a given host.
// cmd_net_ping sends ICMP echo requests and measures round-trip time.
// cmd_net_trace runs a traceroute showing each hop to the destination.
// cmd_net_cert inspects TLS certificates for a given host and port.
// cmd_net_ws opens an interactive WebSocket connection for testing.

// Primitive flow:
// TCP server: tcp_listener.bind("0.0.0.0:8080") -> listener_accept loop -> handle conn
// HTTP server: http_server_std(router, middleware_chain) -> http_server_listen("0.0.0.0:8080")
// HTTP client: http_client_std.client_get("https://api.example.com/data")
//   -> url_parse -> tls_connect -> http_request -> response_read_body -> close
// nc net fetch https://example.com --method POST --body '{"x":1}' --header Accept:application/json
// nc net serve ./public --port 3000 -> serves static files with ETag + gzip
// nc net dns example.com --type MX -> prints MX records with priorities
// nc net cert example.com:443 -> prints certificate chain, expiry, and SANs
// cidr_contains("10.0.0.0/8", "10.1.2.3") -> true

// This defines the Norscode network stdlib: TCP/UDP listeners, HTTP client/server,
// URL parsing, IP/CIDR utilities, typed network errors, and the nc net CLI commands.
